.TH SYSMON 1 "January 2026" "sysmon 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sysmon \- lightweight system resource monitor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sysmon.sh
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sysmon
is a Bash script that displays real-time system usage including CPU, memory, and disk statistics. It can run in single-shot more or continuous monitoring mode.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c", " \-\-cpu 
Display CPU usage percentage and top 5 CPU-consuming processes.
.TP 
.BR \-m ", " \-\-memory 
Display memory usage (total, used, free) and top 5 memory-consuming processes.
.TP 
.BR \-d ", " \-\-disk 
Display disk usage for all mounted filesystems with capacity breakdown.
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all 
Display all metrics: CPU, memory and disk usage combined.
.TP 
.BR \-w ", " \-\-watch 
Enable continuous monitoring mode. Refreshes every SECONDS (must be a positive interger). Press Ctrl+c to exit.
.TP 
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help 
Display help message and usage examples.
.SH EXAMPLES 
.TP 
Show CPU usage:
.B sysmon.sh -c 
.TP 
Show memory usage:
.B sysmon.sh -m 
.TP 
Show all metrics once:
.B sysmon.sh -a
.TP 
Monitor all metrics every 3 seconds:
.B sysmon.sh -a -w 3
.TP 
Show CPU and memory (no disk): 
.B sysmon.sh -c -m 
.TP 
Monitor disk usage every 10 seconds:
.B sysmon.sh -d -w 10
.SH ERROR HANDLING
.B sysmon
will exit with error code 1 if:
.IP \(bu 2
No options are specified
.IP \(bu 2
Invalid watch interval (non-numeric or zero/negative)
.IP \(bu 2
Unkonw option provided
.IP \(bu 2
System commands (top, free, df) are unavailable
.SH DEPENDENCIES
Requires standard Unix tools:
.IP \(bu 2
.B top
(for CPU and process information)
.IP \(bu 2
.B free
(for memory statistics)
.IP \(bu 2
.B ps 
(for process listings)
.IP \(bu 2
.B df 
(for disk usage)
